The paper deals with Zero Shot Learning (ZSL) in the context of multimedia, specifically images and music tracks. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) and Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper proposes a semantic learning model that can embed out-of-vocabulary labels, which involves natural language processing (NLP) techniques. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the Natural Language Processing (cs.CL) and Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories. Finally, the paper proposes a novel approach to multi-label ZSL, which involves machine learning techniques. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category.
